# PostCSS Auto Add Px [![Build Status][ci-img]][ci]

[PostCSS] plugin to add px unit for number of length.

[PostCSS]: https://github.com/postcss/postcss
[ci-img]:  https://travis-ci.org/tomgou/postcss-auto-add-px.svg
[ci]:      https://travis-ci.org/tomgou/postcss-auto-add-px

```
const postcss = require('postcss');
const pxplugin = require('postcss-auto-add-px');
const fs = require('fs');

try{
  fs.readFile('./demo/index.less', (err, css) => {
    postcss([pxplugin()])
      .process(css.toString(), { from: './demo/index.less', to: './demo/dist/index.less' })
      .then(result => {
        fs.writeFile('./demo/dist/index.less', result.css, () => true)
      })
  })
} catch (err) {
  console.log(err)
}
```
## Webpack config
```
{
  test: /\.vue$/,
  loader: 'vue-loader',
  options: {
    vueLoaderConfig,
    postcss: [require('postcss-auto-add-px')(), require('autoprefixer')()]
  }
}
```

## Usage

```js
postcss([ require('postcss-auto-add-px') ])
```

See [PostCSS] docs for examples for your environment.
